column164:
To start, the visual aesthetics were very unique and unusual (the good kind).
I also enjoyed the biblical aspects and the surrealism of it all.
The character's faces were a bit in the "uncanny valley", but I think it was kind of the point.
Most of the negatives I've seen were towards the UI elements and the game itself:
-There was no menu or pause function;
-The dialogue UI (lantern, character, text box) was a bit transparent, so it made them blend in a bit with the background;
-The lantern takes up a lot of screen space making the screen cluttered;
-(nitpick) In the text box, "b" and "h" with the font were similar but besides that, I managed to read without worries;
